Jordaan <a href="https://twitter.com/MichaelJordaan/status/1285463234007441409?s=20" data-v-f87c67ca="">said</a> he is "very proud" of the VALR team because it is "never easy to raise R57m for a startup." This is "undeniable validation of local crypto potential," he added.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
Indeed, much of Africa’s 1.2 billion population remains unbanked, according to the World Bank. And at least 64 crypto and blockchain companies are working to improve the continent's financial inclusion, according to <a href="https://www.theblockresearch.com/mapping-out-the-blockchain-ecosystem-in-africa-37674" data-v-f87c67ca="">The Block Research</a>.&nbsp;
